# ASSERT PIN can only observe state at loop()-call boundaries (TestRunner
# checks pin state once per full run_loop() call, not mid-call) -- and pin 13
# is always LOW by the time any single loop() call returns here (it's
# toggled HIGH then back LOW earlier in the same call). So the HIGH half of
# the toggle is unobservable via ASSERT PIN and is checked via the sketch's
# own printed digitalRead/PINB readout instead, which is a cumulative-buffer
# check and isn't subject to that boundary limitation.
0.3, ASSERT, SERIAL_CONTAINS, "pin13 via digitalRead=1 PINB bit5=1"
0.3, ASSERT, SERIAL_CONTAINS, "pin13 via digitalRead=0 PINB bit5=0"
